cuvm — a CUDA toolkit version manager (nvm for CUDA).

Usage: cuvm [COMMAND]

Commands:
  adopt      Discover and register existing CUDA toolkits in place
  ls         List installed and available CUDA toolkits (installed + `<download available>`)
  ls-remote  List toolkit versions available in the remote registry (alias for `ls --only-downloads`)
  install    Download and install one or more CUDA toolkit versions
  current    Print the currently active bundle handle
  which      Print the absolute toolkit root for a spec
  use        Print env-activation code for a spec (shim evals it)
  default    Set the persistent default (writes the `default` alias)
  alias      Create or update an alias
  unalias    Remove an alias
  pin        Write `.cuda-version` in the current directory
  doctor     Diagnose driver/toolkit/PATH health; exit code is machine-readable
  uninstall  De-register a bundle (adopted installs are not deleted — ADR-005)
  help       Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)

Options:
  -h, --help     Print help
  -V, --version  Print version
